div.div: Not a Nuget package, but a versioned zip file containing the files to be copied into the Application on creation. This includes the json configuration files, the index.cshtml view, App.csproj and Program.cs. The later is critical as it ties the applications code and configuration together using dependency injection.
div.p: Main Nuget package referenced by the Altinn 3 Application Template, and hence the Application. Does not contain any code, but is a package that bundles other packages into a single nuget for easy reference from the template/apps.
Package that contains the standard Rest Api's exposed by Altinn 3 Apps. All http logic is contained within this package.

Primary Nuget package for business logic related to the application and the use of the Altinn 3 Platform. This is ignorant of http and and other protocols exposed by the application ie. it should not have direct dependencies on HttpContext, Cookies etc. It contains interfaces and default implementations for the core functionality.
div.div: Contains standard codelists shared by Altinn 3 Applications like countries, counties, communes etc. Depends on Core package for interfaces defining codelists.

Extends the Altinn 3 Application to use EFormidling as an integration point for incoming instances/data. This is an example of add-on functionality used in some, but far from all, applications. Ie. it's not a part of Core, but rather builds upons and extends the Core functionality by hooking into extensions points /interfaces exposed by the Core package.
